<db:section xml:id="details">
<db:title>Detailed Description</db:title>
<db:para>The <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtquick3d-particles3d-affector3d.xml">Affector3D</db:link> is an abstract base class of affectors like <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtquick3d-particles3d-gravity3d.xml">Gravity3D</db:link>, <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtquick3d-particles3d-wander3d.xml">Wander3D</db:link>, and <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtquick3d-particles3d-pointrotator3d.xml">PointRotator3D</db:link>.</db:para>
<db:para>By default affectors affect all particles in the system, but this can be limited by defining the <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtquick3d-particles3d-affector3d.xml#particles-prop">particles</db:link> list. If the system has multiple affectors, the order of affectors may result in different outcome, as affectors are applied one after another.</db:para>
</db:section>
<db:section xml:id="property-documentation">
<db:title>Property Documentation</db:title>
<db:section xml:id="enabled-prop">
<db:title>enabled : bool</db:title>
<db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:type>bool</db:type>
<db:varname>enabled</db:varname>
<db:modifier>writable</db:modifier>
<db:synopsisinfo role="access">public</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="status">active</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="threadsafeness">unspecified</db:synopsisinfo>
</db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:para>If enabled is set to <db:code>false</db:code>, this affector will not alter any particles. Usually this is used to conditionally turn an affector on or off.</db:para>
<db:para>The default value is <db:code>true</db:code>.</db:para>
</db:section>
<db:section xml:id="particles-prop">
<db:title>particles : List&lt;Particle3D&gt;</db:title>
<db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:type>List&lt;Particle3D&gt;</db:type>
<db:varname>particles</db:varname>
<db:modifier>writable</db:modifier>
<db:synopsisinfo role="access">public</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="status">active</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="threadsafeness">unspecified</db:synopsisinfo>
</db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:para>This list controls which logical particles will be affected. When empty, all particles in the system are affected.</db:para>
</db:section>
<db:section xml:id="system-prop">
<db:title>system : ParticleSystem3D</db:title>
<db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:type>ParticleSystem3D</db:type>
<db:varname>system</db:varname>
<db:modifier>writable</db:modifier>
<db:synopsisinfo role="access">public</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="status">active</db:synopsisinfo>
<db:synopsisinfo role="threadsafeness">unspecified</db:synopsisinfo>
</db:fieldsynopsis>
<db:para>This property defines the <db:link xlink:href="qml-qtquick3d-particles3d-particlesystem3d.xml">ParticleSystem3D</db:link> for the affector. If system is direct parent of the affector, this property does not need to be defined.</db:para>
</db:section>
